{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Cake","content":["Preheat oven to 170°C. Grease and line a round cake tin (Ø 20 cm) with baking paper then set aside.","Place cardamom pods in mixing bowl and chop <nobr>10 sec\/speed 6<\/nobr> to separate seeds. Remove and discard pods, leaving seeds in mixing bowl.","Add sugar and grind <nobr>10 sec\/speed 10<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add cashews and grind <nobr>3 sec\/speed 6<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add butter, yoghurt and eggs then mix <nobr>15 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add flour and mix with aid of spatula <nobr>10 sec\/speed 4<\/nobr>, or until combined. Transfer to prepared cake tin and bake for 55 minutes (170°C), or until a skewer inserted in centre comes out clean. Clean mixing bowl."]},{"title":"Syrup","content":["Place sugar and lime zest in mixing bowl then grind <nobr>20 sec\/speed 9<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add lime juice and water then cook <nobr>5 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/nobr>. Pierce cake all over using wooden skewer and pour sauce over warm cake while still in tin. Allow to cool in tin (approx. 20 minutes) before serving."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Cake","content":["200 g unsalted butter, softened, plus extra for greasing","1 Tbsp cardamom pods (see tips)","240 g sugar","200 g cashew nuts, roasted, unsalted","170 g plain yoghurt","4 medium eggs","240 g self-raising flour"]},{"title":"Syrup","content":["120 g sugar","1 lime, finely grated zest only","1 Tbsp lime juice","90 g water"]}],"id":"r268796","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-SEJa8AIhXkE\/XZWqcVw3roI\/AAAAAAAAfX8\/UohtAuNJivk-1Q5mS4pBlWqYzVUZd553gCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_LTbOOSH7MO0QMP5q.png","title":"Cardamom And Lime Syrup Cake","publishedAt":"2017-11-27T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"8 g","fat":"25 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"50 g","calories":"1898 kJ \/ 452 kcal"},"usefulItems":"round cake tin (Ø 20 cm), baking paper, wooden skewer, oven","hintsAndTricks":["<nobr>2 tsp<\/nobr> ground cardamom can be used instead of cardamom pods. Omit <nobr>step 2<\/nobr> then add ground cardamom with sugar in <nobr>step 3<\/nobr>.","This cake has a strong cardamom flavour. If preferred, reduce cardamom pods to <nobr>2 tsp<\/nobr> and proceed as per recipe."],"basicInfo":["easy","10m","1h 35m","12 portions"]}